  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What profitable business I can start with INR 1 lakh?",
  "response": "Starting a profitable business with INR 1 lakh is certainly feasible, and there are several options you can consider. Here\u2019s a list of business ideas that might fit within this budget:\n\n1. **Online Tutoring**: With the rise of edtech, online tutoring is in demand. If you have expertise in a particular subject, you can start offering classes virtually.\n\n2. **Digital Marketing Agency**: If you have skills in social media management, SEO, or content marketing, you can start an agency helping small businesses grow their online presence.\n\n3. **Food Delivery Service**: If you enjoy cooking, consider starting a meal prep and delivery service. You can also focus on a niche, such as healthy meals or regional cuisine.\n\n4. **Handmade Crafts**: If you're good at crafting, consider selling handmade products such as jewelry, candles, or home decor items online or at local markets.\n\n5. **Dropshipping**: Start an online store without holding inventory. You can sell products through platforms like Shopify and use dropshipping suppliers to fulfill orders.\n\n6. **Mobile Car Wash**: A mobile car wash service requires minimal investment and can yield high returns. All you need are some basic cleaning supplies and transportation.\n\n7. **Affiliate Marketing**: Start a blog or YouTube channel and promote affiliate products. Through this, you can earn a commission for every sale made through your referral.\n\n8. **Pet Sitting or Dog Walking**: If you love animals, this service can be started with minimal investment and requires only marketing your services in your local area.\n\n9. **Freelance Services**: Utilize your skills in writing, graphic design, programming, or photography. Platforms like Upwork or Fiverr can help you find clients.\n\n10. **Event Planning**: If you have excellent organizational skills, offering event planning services can be quite lucrative, whether for weddings, corporate events, or birthday parties.\n\n11. **Fitness Trainer**: If you're passionate about fitness, you can become a personal trainer or start group classes in local parks or via online classes.\n\n12. **Home Cleaning Services**: Start a cleaning service targeting homes or offices in your area. You will need some basic supplies, and marketing can be done through word-of-mouth or local advertising.\n\nTo ensure success, here are a few tips:\n\n- **Research Your Market**: Understand your target audience and competitors.\n- **Create a Business Plan**: Outline your business goals, strategy, and financial projections.\n- **Leverage Online Platforms**: Use social media and online marketplaces to promote your business.\n- **Focus on Quality**: Whether it\u2019s a product or service, quality should be your top priority.\n- **Network**: Connect with other entrepreneurs and potential customers to grow your business.\n\nBefore starting, ensure that you have all the necessary licenses and permits required legally in your area. With careful planning and execution, you can build a profitable business within your budget.",
